   254	    "SUBCHAPTER III - MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS Part B - General Sec. 7656 - "
   255	    "Designation of Crisis Management Team within Department From the U.S. Government "
   256	    "Publishing Office, www.gpo.gov §7656. Designation of Crisis Management Team "
   257	    "within Department (a) Designation of Crisis Management Team The Secretary of "
   258	    "Agriculture shall designate a Crisis Management Team within the Department of "
   259	    "Agriculture, which shall be— (1) composed of senior departmental personnel with "
   260	    "strong subject matter expertise selected from each relevant agency of the "
   261	    "Department; and (2) headed by a team leader with management and communications "
   262	    "skills. (b) Duties of Crisis Management Team The Crisis Management Team shall be "
   263	    "responsible for the following: (1) Developing a Department-wide crisis "
   264	    "management plan, taking into account similar plans developed by other government "
   265	    "agencies and other large organizations, and developing written procedures for "
   266	    "the implementation of the crisis management plan. (2) Conducting periodic "
   267	    "reviews and revisions of the crisis management plan and procedures developed "
   268	    "under paragraph (1). (3) Ensuring compliance with crisis management procedures "
   269	    "by personnel of the Department and ensuring that appropriate Department "
   270	    "personnel are familiar with the crisis management plan and procedures and are "
   271	    "encouraged to bring information regarding crises or potential crises to the "
   272	    "attention of members of the Crisis Management Team. (4) Coordinating the "
   273	    "Department's information gathering and dissemination activities concerning "
   274	    "issues managed by the Crisis Management Team. (5) Ensuring that Department "
   275	    "spokespersons convey accurate, timely, and scientifically sound information "
   276	    "regarding crises or potential crises that can be easily understood by the "
   277	    "general public. (6) Cooperating with, and coordinating among, other Federal "
   278	    "agencies, States, local governments, industry, and public interest groups, "
   279	    "Department activities regarding a crisis. (c) Role in prioritizing certain "
   280	    "research The Crisis Management Team shall cooperate with the Advisory Board in "
   281	    "the prioritization of agricultural research conducted or funded by the "
   282	    "Department regarding animal health, natural disasters, food safety, and other "
   283	    "agricultural issues. (d) Cooperative agreements The Secretary shall seek to "
   284	    "enter into cooperative agreements with other Federal departments and agencies "
   285	    "that have related programs or activities to help ensure consistent, accurate, "
   286	    "and coordinated dissemination of information throughout the executive branch in "
   287	    "the event of a crisis, such as, in the case of a threat to human health from "
   288	    "food-borne pathogens, developing a rapid and coordinated response among the "
   289	    "Department, the Centers for Disease Control, and the Food and Drug "
   290	    "Administration. (Pub. L. 105–185, title VI, §618, June 23, 1998, 112 Stat. 607.)"
